        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 2:52PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marshall, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marshall, Hallsville, Tatum, Beckville, Harleton, Easton, Darco
and Nesbitt.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
